    public interface UiWidgetListBoxField<VALUE>
extends UiWidgetListBase<VALUE>, UiWidgetField<List<VALUE>>, UiWidgetNative, AttributeWriteOptions<VALUE>, AttributeWriteHeightInRows
    This is the interface for a options field widget that represents a list box. Such widget is a simple list that allows to select one or multiple items out of a list of options. Its value is therefore the list of selected items.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Joerg Hohwiller (hohwille at users.sourceforge.net)
    See Also:
    UiWidgetOptionListTable

    • Method Detail

      • getAriaRole

        RoleListbox getAriaRole()
        This method gets the Accessibility.WAI_ARIA role of this object.
        ATTENTION:
        A reasonable UI framework (e.g. when using UiWidget) is supposed to provide high-level widgets and support setting the according Role and their attributes automatically. Therefore users should only use this for special situations e.g. for setting aria-hidden intentionally for a visible object.
        Specified by:
        getAriaRole in interface AttributeReadAriaRole
        Returns:
        the Role or null if NOT set.
        See Also:
        Accessibility

      • getValue

        List<VALUE> getValue()
        This method gets the value of this object. This will typically be a newly created object.
        ATTENTION:
        If the current value entered by the user can NOT be parsed, this method will catch and ignore the exception and return null instead. If you want to do validation and give feedback to the user please use AttributeReadValueAdvanced.getValueOrException(Object) instead. However, there are higher-level ways to do this such as getValueAndValidate.
        IMPORTANT:
        To prevent problems with undesired modifications of values there is a general copy on get strategy. This way you can set values and allow them to be modified in the UI without side-effects on the original value. This is especially important for composite custom widgets (e.g. editors) to allow the user to modify business entities and modifications can still be cancelled and changed will be reverted. All objects that are (potentially) modified by the widgets will be copied. Therefore it is even safe to modify the result of this method in most cases. However, tree widgets build an excuse and use a copy on set/retrieve strategy.
        Specified by:
        getValue in interface AttributeReadValue<List<VALUE>>
        Specified by:
        getValue in interface AttributeReadValueAdvanced<List<VALUE>>
        Specified by:
        getValue in interface UiWidgetWithValue<List<VALUE>>
        Returns:
        the value of this object. May be null unless otherwise stated.
